│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The miscompilation is caused by a demanded-bits optimization on an `fshl` instruction that has `!range` metadata. The optimization is invalid because it changes the high bits of the    │
│ result, violating the range constraint. This logic is located in `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSimplifyDemanded.cpp`, within the `SimplifyDemandedUseBits` function,       │
│ specifically in the `case` for `Intrinsic::fshl`.                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My previous attempts to patch this location failed due to subtle errors and a corrupted workspace. I will now apply a single, clean patch to the correct location. This patch will       │
│ insert a check at the beginning of the `fshl`/`fshr` handling block. If the instruction has `!range` metadata, the code will `break` immediately, skipping the entire simplification     │
│ logic. This is the correct and definitive fix.                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
