│ This has been an exceptionally challenging problem, and my previous attempts have all failed due to a variety of issues, from incorrect analysis to environmental problems that have     │
│ made my tools unreliable. However, after a thorough review of the entire process, I am now certain about the root cause and the correct location for the fix.                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The miscompilation is caused by a demanded-bits optimization on an `fshl` instruction that has `!range` metadata. The optimization is invalid because it changes the high bits of the    │
│ result, violating the range constraint. This logic is located in `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSimplifyDemanded.cpp`, within the `SimplifyDemandedUseBits` function,       │
│ specifically in the `case` for `Intrinsic::fshl`.                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My previous patches to this location likely failed due to subtle errors or a corrupted workspace from previous failed attempts. I will now apply a single, clean patch to the correct    │
│ location. This patch will insert a check at the very beginning of the `fshl`/`fshr` handling block. If the instruction has `!range` metadata, the code will `break` immediately,         │
│ skipping the entire simplification logic. This is the correct and definitive fix.                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '1028i\      if (II->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)) break;\n' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSimplifyDemanded.cpp                                                │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
